MilesMickelson.com

My mission for this project was to develop a high-quality website and showcase my creative ingenuity. To do so, I used Node, React, Parcel, Sass, and a custom ES-Lint AirBNB configuration for clean and concise code. This website is fully responsive across all screen sizes, without the use of a single media query, and maintains the utmost browser compatibility. I was able to maximize performance, accessibility, best practices, and search engine optimization by utilizing the Lighthouse module, the final audit score–and outline, are displayed below. Furthermore, Google Analytics integrated for continuous improvement –view repository.

Performance - All files and images are compressed and served in a gzip, brotli, or select image format to decrease the total size and loading time. Through asynchronous downloading in the background the HTML parses without disruption or waiting, allowing the presentation of the website sooner. Once the initial loading phase is complete, automatic pre-rendering for the remainder of the pages begins, allowing a complete download before you navigate to them.

Accessibility - Utilizing correct aria attributes with valid values and a proper HTML structure with landmark elements, the site is 100% accessible. Allowing for navigation with a keyboard and voice assistant technology, giving the user informative feedback on essential and informative elements only, and quickly.

Best Practices - Employs HTTPS for secure server communication and HTML attributes for helping to prevent vulnerabilities. All images displayed with the correct aspect ratio and no browser errors logged into the console.

Search Engine Optimization - Fulfills necessary elements with proper attributes and descriptive text to increase search optimization rating. All link targets and text is sized appropriately for ease of navigating and reading.
